he RNGs verification function\n   350→\n   351→**Item**: Phase C, item 2 — Add verification function to game-engine\n   352→\n   353→**What was done**:\n   354→- Added to `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`:\n   355→  - `RoundSettledEvent` interface — typed representation of the on-chain RoundSettled event fields (tier, roundNumber, winner, randomness, winningSlot, totalEntries, payoutAmount, feeAmount, vrfRequestKey)\n   356→  - `LordVerificationResult` interface — verification result with valid flag, error messages, and computed values\n   357→  - `verifyLordRound(event, players)` — re-derives winning slot from VRF randomness using `determineWinnerFromRandomness`, verifies it matches event's claimed slot and winner, also checks fee = 3% of total pool\n   358→  - `calculateJackpotPayout(tier, totalEntries)` — computes winner payout (pool × 0.97), mirrors coinflip's `calculatePotentialPayout` but for N-player jackpot\n   359→- Updated `packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`:\n   360→  - Added exports: `verifyLordRound`, `calculateJackpotPayout`, `RoundSettledEvent`, `LordVerificationResult`\n   361→- Design decision: verification lives in game-engine (not fairness package) because fairness package is HMAC/crash-specific while VRF verification uses `@solana/web3.js` types (PublicKey)\n   362→\n   363→**Verification**: `pnpm typecheck` — 17/17 packages pass. `pnpm lint` — 17/17 packages pass (0 errors).\n   364→\n   365→**Status**: Done\n   366→\n   367→## Iteration 12 — 2026-02-26T23:10:00Z — OK\n   368→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   369→\n   370→## Iteration 12 — 2026-02-26T23:09:27Z — OK\n   371→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   372→\n   373→## Iteration 13 — Sync lordofrngs IDL to anchor-client package\n   374→\n   375→**Item**: Phase C, item 3 — Sync IDL and export typed program interface\n   376→\n   377→**What was done**:\n   378→- Ran `anchor build -p lordofrngs` — confirmed IDL at `solana/target/idl/lordofrngs.json` and types at `solana/target/types/lordofr